To compile program, navigate to directory and type
  make
into a terminal.

To run as chat server, type
  ./chat
into a terminal. This starts the chat server and lists the port and ip address of the server.

To connect to the chat server, type
  ./chat -p <port number> -s <server ip address>
into a terminal. This starts the chat client and connects it to the chat server with the given port number and ip address.